          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "The most common cause of limp in a child between 3-10 years is transient synovitis of hip.\nHowever, among the given options Perthe's disease is the best answer as Perthes disease is the second most common cause of limp in a child between 5-10 years."
