          "explanation": "Skeletal manifestations of congenital syphilis Clutton's joints - Painless sterile effusions in the knees or elbows Parrot's joints - Effusion with epiphysitis and epiphyseal separation Erosion of the nasal boneThickening and expansion of the finger phalanges (dactylitis) Higoumenaki's sign - Bilateral enlargement of sternal end of the clavicle Saber tibia, Scaphoid scapula (Refer: Mohindra's Fundamentals of Ohopedics, 2nd edition, pg no. 291)",
          "hint": "Topic: All India exam"
