          "explanation": "Paget's disease occurs after 40 years of age and is more common in males.\nAlkaline phosphatase (ALP) is raised and calcium & phosphate are normal.\nThe usual malignancy complicating Paget's disease is osteosarcoma. There are some reports of cases of chondrosarcoma as a complication of Paget's disease."
