          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Muscles attached to greater tuberosity are.\n\n\nSupraspinatus: - Helps in the initial range of abduction.\nInfraspinatous, Teres minor : - External (lateral) rotation.\n\n\nTherefore, these movements are affected in fracture greater tuberosity.\nMuscle attached to lesser tuberosity is subscapularis (an internal or medial rotator of shoulder joint). So, movement affected in lesser tuberosity fracture is an internal rotation."
