          "explanation": "Neutral triangle of the calcaneum\n\nWithin the trabeculae of calcaneus lies the neutral triangle, an area directly below the distal edge of a posterior facet.\nThe base of the triangle is the weakest, most vulnerable portion of the calcaneum.\nAxial impaction of the talus into the calcaneum results in a vertical fracture through the neutral triangle, and it represents the primary fracture line."
