          "explanation": "Ans. is 'a' i.e., Fracture supracondylar humerus o Compartment syndrome is most commonly caused by extremity fracturesSupracondylar fracture of humerus is the most common cause is children.Crush injuries to forearm are the most common cause in adults.Other injuries are fracture both bones forearm, elbow dislocation.",
