          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Ulnar nerve causes ulnar claw hand.\nThere is sensory loss of medial one & half digits.\nThere is weakness of grip due to paralysis of intrinsic muscles, FCU and medial half of FDP.\nThere is loss of flexion at MCP joint due to paralysis of lumbricals and interossei.\nAdduction of thumb is lost (not abduction)."
