          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Ans. is 'b' i.e., Zygomatiomaxillary fracture o Zygomaticomaxillary complex (ZMC) fractures, also known as a tripod, tetrapod, quadripod, malar or trimalar fractures, are seen in the setting of traumatic injury to the face. They comprise fractures of the:# Zygomatic arch# Inferior orbital rim, and anterior and posterior maxillary sinus walls# Lateral orbital rim",
