          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Most of the time (80%) aneurysmal bone cyst is primary, and no other pathology is found.\nSecondary aneurysmal bone cysts (20%) occurs when bone changes of aneurysmal bone cyst occur in a pre-existing lesion:-\n\n\nGiant cell tumors (osteoclastoma) : - Most common      \nOsteoblastoma \nSimple bone cyst\nNon-ossifying fibroma  \nTelangiectatic osteosarcoma\nMetastasis\nFibrous dysplasia\nPaget's disease\n Chondromyxoid fibroma\nChondroblastoma"
