          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Ans is 'b' i.e. after 2 years Tendon transfers: are done to equalize an unbalanced paralysis or to use the motor power of working muscles for more useful functions. It is not done before 5 yrs of age as the child has to be manageable enough to be taught proper exercises.",
          "hint": "Topic: Nervous System"
