          "explanation": "Congenital high scapula (Sprengel&;s shoulder)The congenital high scapula is an uncommon congenital deformity characterized by an abnormally high position and relative fixity fixity of scapulaThe anomaly represents a failure of the scapula of the scapula to descend during development to its normal thoracic position(Refer: Mohindra's Fundamentals of Ohopedics, 2nd edition, pg no. 380)",
