          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Triple Ahrodesis: Fusion of three joints Talonavicular - most difficult to fuse Talocalcaneal Calcaneocuboid Indicated only if there is a strong contraindication to ahroplasty (eg, previous infection) or to salvage a failed ahroplasty Indication: >10 yrs of age for treatment of CTEV",
          "hint": "Topic: Pediatric Ohopedics"
