          "explanation": "(osteogenic sarcoma) (218-M) (185-Appley's 8th)* Osteogenic sarcoma is highly malignant primary bone tumour - (Common in Age 15-25 years)* Osteoid osteoma - is the commonest true benign tumour of the bone.",
          "hint": "Topic: Bone Tumour"
