          "explanation": "It can be used in the setting of painful osteoporotic compression fractures, pathologic fractures from underlying neoplasms, or structurally compromised veebrae. Percutaneous veebroplasty (PVP) usually involves percutaneous injection of PMMA into the veebral bodies Percutaneous cementoplasty (also known as veebral packing or veebroplasty) with acrylic cement (polymethylmethacrylate ) A procedure aimed at preventing veebral body collapse and pain in patients with pathologic veebral bodies. Percutaneous cementoplasty is a promising therapeutic technique for pain control in patients with bone failure Applications It can be used in the treatment of: Severe painful osteoporosis with loss of height and/or with compression fractures of veebral bodies 1) Insufficiency fracture 2) Aggressive hemangioma 3) Veebral multiple myeloma 4) Painful veebral body tumors and acetabular tumors 5) Veebral metastases Ref essential ohopaedic maheshwari and mhaskar 9TH EDp 270<img alt=\"\" src=\" />",
