          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Diastematomyelia (split cord malformation), refers to a type of spinal dysraphism (spina bifida occulta) when there is a longitudinal split in the spinal cord. Diastematomyelia signs and symptoms of tethered cord, although patients with mild type II may be minimally affected or entirely asymptomatic. Presenting symptoms include: leg weakness, low back pain, scoliosis, incontinence Associated anomalies including: meningocoele, neurenteric cyst, dermoid, clubfoot, spinal cord lipoma, haemangioma overlying spine. Type I: duplicated dural sac, with common midline spur (osseous or fibrous) and usually symptomatic Type II: single dural sac containing both hemicords; impairment less marked.",
          "hint": "Topic: Spinal Injury"
