          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "The bone is made up of bone cells and extracellular matrix.The matrix consists oftwo types of materials,organic and inorganic. The organic matrix is formed by the collagen,which forms 30-35% of dry weight of a bone. The inorganic matrix is primarily calcium and phophorus salts,especially hydroxyapatite .It constitutes about 65-70% of dry weight of a bone. ref:maheswari,5th edition page no.9",
