          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "A tension band wire is a form of ohopaedic internal fixation method used to conve distraction forces into compression forces, promoting bone healing. Uses: Olecranon fracture Patella fracture Medial malleolus fracture ref : maheswari 9th ed",
