          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Ans. is 'd' i.e.Mid prone * Treatment of both bones forearm:Conservative - CR & immobilisation in an above elbow POPConservative treatment is sufficient in children because in them this fracture is often undisplaced.But in adults they are notoriously prone to severe displacement.OR & IF -Is required especially in adults.During OR & IF the radius & ulna should be approached through separate incision.",
